verbose_text: Furthermore, the PTH level was significantly higher in the control positive group (69.11 +/- 1.11) than in both of those intervention groups T and R (50.13 +/- 0.96 and 58.87 +/- 1.01b), which showed difference from each normal control (45.29 +/- 0.92) and oral group (41.21 +/- 0.80) (p < 0.05).
